SilverStripe CMS  Module (Socializer)

This is a prewview alpha of the Socializer 4 SilverStripe,  module which whill
enable automatically inserting Social Bookmarks

This modules written by Daniel Suzan(WaRHoTDoG)

To Install

1- Rename the extracted directory to "Socializer" and place i nthe root of your
SilverStripe Installation

2. Run /dev/build/

3- Configure the module for your preference in _config.php

/* View the _config.php for more information */
SocializerAdmin::set_InviteFriendEmail(true); // false
SocializerAdmin::set_PrintPage(true); // false
SocializerAdmin::set_SocializerTheme('wpzoom'); // VSM
SocializerAdmin::set_SocializerThemeSize('32px'); // 16px,24px,32px,48px,64px
SocializerAdmin::set_LibraryUse('MT'); //JQuery  MT  Prototype
SocializerAdmin::set_SimpleSocializer(true); // false

4- Add the variable '$SocializerBar' to the position you want display
if you user SipleSocializer enable (true) need $Form variable

5- Go to Admin->Socializer  and add you social sites

6- Go To Behaviour and check Show ShareIcons on this page.
